description: An alternative to `<Select native />` with a much smaller bundle size footprint.

children.description:
The option elements to populate the select with.
Can be some `<option>` elements.

classes.description:
Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
See [CSS API](#css) below for more details.

IconComponent.description: The icon that displays the arrow.

input.description: An `Input` element; does not have to be a material-ui specific `Input`.

onChange.description: Callback function fired when a menu item is selected.

tags.title: param
tags.description:
The event source of the callback.
You can pull out the new value by accessing `event.target.value` (string).
tags.name: event

value.description: The input value. The DOM API casts this to a string.

name: NativeSelect

descriptions.root: Styles applied to the select component `root` class.
descriptions.select: Styles applied to the select component `select` class.
descriptions.filled: Styles applied to the select component if `variant="filled"`.
descriptions.outlined: Styles applied to the select component if `variant="outlined"`.
descriptions.selectMenu: Styles applied to the select component `selectMenu` class.
descriptions.disabled: Pseudo-class applied to the select component `disabled` class.
descriptions.icon: Styles applied to the icon component.
descriptions.iconOpen: Styles applied to the icon component if the popup is open.
descriptions.iconFilled: Styles applied to the icon component if `variant="filled"`.
descriptions.iconOutlined: Styles applied to the icon component if `variant="outlined"`.
